Q : Why we Use docker ?
Ans : Suppose a developer’s system has 8GB RAM and 256GB storage, and the code runs fine there.
      But when the same code is given to a client with 4GB RAM and 128GB storage, it may not work because of environment
 	  differences (like OS, Java version, or dependencies).
      To solve this, we use Docker — it containerizes the whole project (application + dependencies) into a single image.
      We then push this image to Docker Hub, and the client just pulls and runs it — the app works the same on all 
	  machines.

💬 Short Version (for interview):

We use Docker to remove environment dependency issues.
It packages the app and its dependencies into a container, so it runs the same in development, testing, and production.
Docker runs the same container image everywhere — dev, test, or production.

